'''The Petersburg State Transport University''' (<U+041F><U+0435><U+0442><U+0435><U+0440><U+0431><U+0443><U+0440><U+0433><U+0441><U+043A><U+0438><U+0439> <U+0433><U+043E><U+0441><U+0443><U+0434><U+0430><U+0440><U+0441><U+0442><U+0432><U+0435><U+043D><U+043D><U+044B><U+0439> <U+0443><U+043D><U+0438><U+0432><U+0435><U+0440><U+0441><U+0438><U+0442><U+0435><U+0442> <U+043F><U+0443><U+0442><U+0435><U+0439> <U+0441><U+043E><U+043E><U+0431><U+0449><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+044F>, abbreviated <U+041F><U+0413><U+0423><U+041F><U+0421>) is a higher education institution specializing in [[railway transport]]. Before 1990 it was known as "Leningrad Institute of Railway Engineers" (<U+041B><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+043D><U+0433><U+0440><U+0430><U+0434><U+0441><U+043A><U+0438><U+0439> <U+0438><U+043D><U+0441><U+0442><U+0438><U+0442><U+0443><U+0442> <U+0438><U+043D><U+0436><U+0435><U+043D><U+0435><U+0440><U+043E><U+0432> <U+0436><U+0435><U+043B><U+0435><U+0437><U+043D><U+043E><U+0434><U+043E><U+0440><U+043E><U+0436><U+043D><U+043E><U+0433><U+043E> <U+0442><U+0440><U+0430><U+043D><U+0441><U+043F><U+043E><U+0440><U+0442><U+0430> abbreviated <U+041B><U+0418><U+0418><U+0416><U+0422>). The main building is located on [[Moskovsky Prospekt]], number 9. The institution educates engineers, who built, develop and maintain railroads throughout the Russian Federation.

Its earliest precursors date back to 1798-1809, as a part of the training provided in  the Department of Water Communications by NP Rumyantsev.<ref>{{cite web
